    "Here‚Äôs a **clean, practical ranking from healthiest ‚Üí least healthy**, based on **hydration quality, sugar content, calories, long-term metabolic risk, dental impact, and evidence quality**. I‚Äôll also give each a **health score (10 = best)** and a short, honest verdict.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## ü•á **1. Plain Water** ‚Äî **10/10**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why:**\n",
    "\n",
    "* Best hydration efficiency\n",
    "* Zero calories, zero sugar, zero additives\n",
    "* Supports kidney, metabolic, and cardiovascular health\n",
    "\n",
    "**Bottom line:** Nothing beats it. This is the benchmark everything else fails to exceed.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## ü•à **2. Unsweetened Sparkling Water** ‚Äî **9/10**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why:**\n",
    "\n",
    "* Hydrates just as well as still water\n",
    "* No sugar, no calories\n",
    "* Helps people replace soda\n",
    "\n",
    "**Watch out for:**\n",
    "\n",
    "* Mild bloating for some people\n",
    "* Frequent acidic exposure can *slightly* affect enamel\n",
    "\n",
    "**Bottom line:** Excellent daily alternative if plain water bores you.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## ü•â **3. Oral Rehydration Solutions (low-sugar, medical-grade)** ‚Äî **8.5/10**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why:**\n",
    "\n",
    "* Optimally balanced electrolytes\n",
    "* Superior for dehydration, illness, heavy sweating\n",
    "\n",
    "**Downside:**\n",
    "\n",
    "* Unnecessary for normal daily hydration\n",
    "\n",
    "**Bottom line:** Targeted tool. Fantastic when needed, pointless when not.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## **4. Unsweetened Tea (black, green, herbal)** ‚Äî **8/10**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why:**\n",
    "\n",
    "* Hydrates effectively\n",
    "* Contains beneficial polyphenols\n",
    "* Very low calorie\n",
    "\n",
    "**Watch out for:**\n",
    "\n",
    "* Excess caffeine ‚Üí dehydration, sleep issues\n",
    "\n",
    "**Bottom line:** Strong everyday option if caffeine intake is controlled.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## **5. Low-Fat Milk** ‚Äî **7.5/10**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why:**\n",
    "\n",
    "* Excellent post-exercise hydration\n",
    "* Provides protein, calcium, electrolytes\n",
    "* Proven rehydration efficiency\n",
    "\n",
    "**Downside:**\n",
    "\n",
    "* Calories\n",
    "* Not ideal if lactose intolerant\n",
    "\n",
    "**Bottom line:** More ‚Äúnutrition + hydration‚Äù than pure hydration.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## **6. Coconut Water (unsweetened)** ‚Äî **7/10**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why:**\n",
    "\n",
    "* Naturally high in potassium\n",
    "* Better than sports drinks for mild rehydration\n",
    "\n",
    "**Downside:**\n",
    "\n",
    "* Still contains sugar\n",
    "* Less sodium than ideal for heavy sweating\n",
    "\n",
    "**Bottom line:** Fine occasionally; overhyped as a miracle drink.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## **7. Sports Drinks (typical commercial versions)** ‚Äî **4.5/10**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why:**\n",
    "\n",
    "* Helpful **only** for prolonged, intense exercise\n",
    "\n",
    "**Problems:**\n",
    "\n",
    "* High sugar\n",
    "* Calorie-dense\n",
    "* Linked to obesity, diabetes, tooth decay when consumed routinely\n",
    "\n",
    "**Bottom line:** If you‚Äôre not training hard for >60‚Äì90 minutes, skip them.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## **8. Diet Soda** ‚Äî **4/10**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why it ranks this high:**\n",
    "\n",
    "* No sugar, no calories\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why it‚Äôs still bad:**\n",
    "\n",
    "* Acidic ‚Üí enamel damage\n",
    "* Sweeteners may disrupt appetite regulation\n",
    "* No hydration benefit beyond water replacement\n",
    "\n",
    "**Bottom line:** Less harmful than regular soda, but not a health drink.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## **9. Regular Soda (cola, soft drinks)** ‚Äî **2/10**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why:**\n",
    "\n",
    "* Zero nutritional value\n",
    "* Very high sugar load\n",
    "* Strong links to obesity, diabetes, fatty liver, cavities\n",
    "\n",
    "**Bottom line:** One of the worst daily hydration choices possible.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## **10. Energy Drinks (sugary + high caffeine)** ‚Äî **1/10**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why:**\n",
    "\n",
    "* Sugar + caffeine overload\n",
    "* Can worsen dehydration\n",
    "* Associated with heart rhythm issues, anxiety, sleep disruption\n",
    "\n",
    "**Bottom line:** Worst of both worlds ‚Äî hydration failure and metabolic harm.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## ‚úÖ **Quick Summary Table**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Rank | Drink                         | Score |\n",
